                    <msContents>
                        <summary>This is one of the most famous books of Mullā Ṣadrā. Considering its comprehensiveness and its influence on the field of Islamic philosophy, 
                            the book has acquired a unique position in the recent centuries, to the extent that many works of the succeeding generations of Islamic philosophers were
                            either derived from or inspired by this work. Mullā Ṣadrā has created his book's plot based on the four journeys of the mystics:
                            (1) Journey from the People towards the Truth, (2) Journey towards the Truth from the Truth, (3) Journey from the Truth towards the People, and (4) Journey towards the Truth within the People.
                            The book is compiled in four volumes, as follows: first volume, <foreign xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Fī al-umūr al-ʿāmmah</foreign>;
                            second volume, <foreign xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Fī al-ʿilm al-ṭabīʿī</foreign>; third volume, <foreign xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Fī al-ʿilm al-ilāhī</foreign>; and fourth volume, 
                            <foreign xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Fī ʿilm al-nafs min al-mabdaʾ ilá al-maʿād</foreign>. The current copy is the second book of the third journey: The Journey towards the Truth from the Truth.
                            </summary>
                        <msItem>
                            <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                            <note type="content-genre">Islamic Philosophy</note>
                            <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">al-Asfār al-ʾarbaʿah</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ara">الاسفار الاربعه</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">al-Ḥikmat al-mutaʿālīyah fī al-asfār al-ʿaqlīyah al-ʾarbaʿah</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ara" type="alt">الحکمه المتعالیه فی الاسفار العقلیه الاربعه</title>
                            <author key="n81035993‏" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/98174078">
                                <persName xml:lang="eng" type="standard"></persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">‎‎‎Ṣadr al-Dīn Shīrāzī, Muḥammad ibn Ibrāhīm, -1641</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">‎</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ara" type="standard">صدر الدين الشيرازى، محمد بن ابراهيم، -۱۶۴۱</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ara" type="alt">صدر الدين الشيرازى، محمد بن ابراهيم، ۹۷۹-۱۰۵۰ق/۱۵۷۱-۱۶۴۰</persName>
                                <addName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="laqab">Mullā Ṣadrā</addName>
                                <addName xml:lang="ara" type="laqab">ملا صدرا</addName>
                                <addName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="kunyah"></addName>
                                <addName xml:lang="ara" type="kunyah"></addName>
                                <addName xml:lang="ara" type="khitab"/>
                                <addName xml:lang="ara" type="nisbah"/>
                            </author>
                            <note xml:lang="eng">  
                            </note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="ara">بسمله، کتاب الثانی فی السفر من الحق الی الحق. الحمد لله الذی انار بوجوب و وجوده وجوه الکاینات و اشرق بنور ذاته… امّا بعد
                                فهذا شروع فی طور آخر من الحکمه و المعرفه و هو تجرید النظر الی ذرات الموجودات و تحقیق وجود المفارقات و الالهیات المسمی بمعرفه الربوبیه…
                            </incipit>
                            <explicit xml:lang="ara">… و ما تجده النفس بل توجده باذن الله من صور الاجرام العظیمه و الافلاک الجسیمه الساکنه و المتحرکه و البلاد
                                الکثیره و خلایقها و احوالها و صفاتها فی طرفه العین هان علیه التصدیق.
                            </explicit>
                            <colophon xml:lang="ara">تمت الکتاب المستطاب بیستم شهر جمادی‌الاول سنه ۱۱۳۹ هجری… کاتب حروف اضعف عبادلله… جلال‌الدین محمد است والسلام
                            </colophon>
